node.name: Horse Shoe
node.title: Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Beanie Black
node.description:
The Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Beanie Black features a classic black colorway and is made from high-quality acrylic knit, ensuring warmth and comfort during colder seasons.

The beanie offers a rib-knitted texture for added warmth and durability. Designed to fit both men and women, the Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Beanie comes in a single size, ensuring a comfortable and snug fit. Chrome Hearts is renowned for its premium craftsmanship and distinctive aesthetic, blending Gothic and biker influences with high-end materials. The brand has a rich history dating back to its founding in the 1980s by Richard Stark, and it has since become a symbol of luxury and individuality.

One special feature the StockX team loves about the Horse Shoe Beanie Black is the attention to detail in the embroidery. The white Chrome Hearts Cross Logo stands out against the black backdrop. The Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Beanie Black was released in April of 2021 with a retail price of $125.

node.description:
The Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Floral Hoodie Black is one of the unisex hoodies that continues to attract high volume of sales for Chrome Hearts since its launch.
​
Two main materials are used in the construction of Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Floral Hoodie Black. The largest percentage of the material that makes up the hoodies is cotton, which occupies 80% of the total materials. The second material is recycled polyester, which occupies 20% of the material used in its construction. The hoodies is all-black with a wide logo of Chrome Hearts around the coral cross sleeves.
​
The Chrome Hearts Horse Shoe Floral Hoodie Black was first released on July 10, 2020. The price of the hoodie at the time of its debut was $550.

node.name: What The
node.title: Jordan 5 Retro What The
node.description:
To honor the 30th Anniversary of the Jordan 5, Jordan Brand added a "What The?" treatment to its catalog with the Jordan 5 What The. This design boasts a mix of materials and details from Jumpman’s best Non-OG Jordan 5 colorways, including the Tokyo, Shanghai, Raging Bull, Bel-Air, Laser, Green Bean, Olive, and Quai 54 colorways.

In true mismatched fashion, each foot of the Jordan 5 What The showcases a different look. On the right, yellow suede from the Tokyo 5 smothers the upper atop a purple and blue speckled Belair 5 midsole with a patterned interior pulled from the Jordan 5 Olive. On the left, red suede tributing the Raging Bull Jordan 5 covers the upper atop a black, grey, and lime green sole that references the Quai 54 iteration. Heel embroidery nodding to the Shanghai and Tokyo models, icy translucent outsoles, and 3M reflective tongues complete this scrambled iteration.

The Jordan 5 What The released in November of 2020 and retailed for $220.

node.name: Win Like 96
node.title: Jordan 11 Retro Win Like 96
node.description: Please note: the Air Jordan 11 Retro Win Like ‘96 sneakers do not include 72 wins and a championship banner (sorry to rub it in Warriors fans). These 11s were part of a historic NBA season for one of the most historic players in the game. Needless to say they are a must own for any MJ fan. The shoe features a mix of patent leather, mesh, and Zoom Air cushioning, and was released in December of 2017 in a full family run of sizes.

node.title: Jordan 11 Retro 72-10
node.description:
The Air Jordan 11 Retro 72-10 introduced a minimalist design with transparent outsole, clean white midsole, and the patent mudguard that defines the Jordan 11 silhouette.
​
This Retro 72 10 features a premium tumbled leather upper with microfiber suede and patent leather overlays. The design also includes a red and black carbon fiber shank plate. A gym red Jumpman logo appears at the heel and tongue, and the sneaker sits atop a white Phylon midsole, with full-length Air-sole cushioning, and on a translucent rubber outsole.
​
The Air Jordan 11 Retro 72-10 was released on the 12th of December 2015, and originally retailed for $220.

node.name: Cap and Gown
node.title: Jordan 11 Retro Cap and Gown
node.description: Cue up the Vitamin C (what up ‘90s kids) and grab a pair of the Jordan 11 Retro Cap and Gowns to strut across that graduation stage. Also known as the "Prom Nights" these come in a clean all-black colorway, and pay homage to Michael Jordan’s original design influence of wanting a basketball sneaker that he could also wear off-court, with a nice suit. Representing graduation ceremonies across the country, these "Cap and Gown" XI’s feature a suede upper with patent leather detailing, a black metal "Jumpman" logo on the ankle and rope laces inspired by graduation cords. These released in May of 2018, at, $250 and came exclusively in men’s sizes, in special packaging. If you’re a fan of the AJ 11, this pair is another must-have.

node.name: Pink Blast
node.title: Nike Mercurial Superfly 7 Elite Mbappe Rose FG Pink Blast
node.description:
The Nike Mercurial Superfly 7 Elite Mbappe Rose FG Pink Blast is a football boot that was designed in collaboration with French footballer Kylian Mbappe.

The upper of the Mercurial Superfly 7 Elite Mbappe Rose FG Pink Blast is made from Nike Flyknit material, which provides a comfortable and snug fit. The shoe has a Pink Blast colorway with white and black accents. The Mercurial Superfly 7 also features a dynamic fit collar that wraps around the ankle, providing extra support and lockdown for your foot. The soleplate is made from a mix of nylon and fiberglass, which is not only lightweight but also provides a strong and stable base for your foot.

We think that the most notable feature of the shoe is its outsole. It features Nike's All Conditions Control (ACC) technology, which provides excellent traction and control in both wet and dry conditions. The Nike Mercurial Superfly 7 Elite Mbappe Rose FG Pink Blast was released on 9th October 2020 for $292.

node.name: Off-White Black (TD)
node.title: Nike Air Max 90 Off-White Black (TD)
node.description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Off-White Black TD is a toddler-sized sneaker from Virgil Abloh’s Off-White and Nike collaboration.

This Air Max 90 sneaker features an all-Black upper made of suede and synthetic with White detailing on Swoosh with a stitched outline and Orange accents on the tongue stitching, Swoosh patch, and tongue tag branding. Other details include a partially detached heel tab, black taped seams, and Off-White branding on the insole. A Black sole unit with Max Air cushioning completes the design. Each pair comes with Off-White tissue paper, a Blue Off-White zip tie, and flat White laces.

What our experts love about this sneaker is its design and colorway. The all-Black upper showcasing Abloh’s trademark aesthetic on the deconstructed look with the stitching and detached heel tab makes this sneaker stand out. The Nike Air Max 90 Off-White Black TD was made available on February 7th, 2019, for a retail price of $75.

node.name: Black Silver
node.title: Reebok Answer 5 Black Silver
node.description:
The Reebok Answer 5 Black Silver pays homage to the 2001 signature silhouette of basketball player Allen Iverson, also known as "The Answer," with a slightly altered OG colorway.

A glossy patent leather toe box meets a black tumbled leather vamp on the upper of this Reebok Answer 5. The lacing system is feature-full, with black laces, punched eyelets with a plastic reinforcement on the collar, and silver leather sheathing covering a mesh padded tongue. The silver overlay has several logos, including an "I3" that re-tells Iverson’s prowess in the court. DMX writings highlight the shoe’s use of DMX cushioning technology on the sole. A hook-and-loop strap tops off the black heel.

What stands out in the Reebok Answer 5 Black Silver? Our experts adore the silver-on-black colorway on this sneaker. Iverson’s branding, including an "I3" motif on the tongue logo and a handwritten signature on the collar, gives these kicks a befitting character. These shoes were released on October 18th, 2019, for $140.

node.name: Black Toe
node.title: Reebok Question Mid Black Toe
node.description: The Reebok Question Mid Black Toe is a classic basketball shoe that has been updated with a sleek and modern design. The shoe features a black leather upper with white accents on the toe box, midsole, and outsole. The iconic Reebok logo is prominently displayed on the side of the shoe in white. The materials used in the construction of the Reebok Question Mid Black Toe are of the highest quality, ensuring durability and comfort. The leather upper is soft and supple, while the midsole provides excellent cushioning and support. Released on April 10th, 2020, the Reebok Question Mid Black Toe is priced at $150, making it an affordable option for those looking for a stylish and functional basketball shoe. Something we love about the Reebok Question Mid Black Toe is its timeless design that pays homage to the original Question Mid while incorporating modern elements. Our experts think the best features of the shoe are its high-quality materials, excellent cushioning, and support. Overall, we love the Reebok Question Mid Black Toe for its combination of style and performance, making it a great choice for both on and off the court.
